The AWS Well-Architected Framework is a set of best practices for designing, building, and operating reliable, secure, efficient, and cost-effective applications on AWS. It is based on six pillars:

Operational Excellence: This pillar focuses on ensuring that your applications are reliable, scalable, and manageable.

Security: This pillar focuses on protecting your applications and data from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, disruption, modification, or destruction.

Reliability: This pillar focuses on ensuring that your applications are highly available and can withstand disruptions.

Performance Efficiency: This pillar focuses on optimizing the performance of your applications and ensuring that they use resources efficiently.

Cost Optimization: This pillar focuses on reducing the cost of running your applications on AWS.

Sustainability: This pillar focuses on designing and operating your applications in a sustainable way that minimizes environmental impact.


