S3 is a object storage


Region-specific services: These services can only be used in a specific AWS region. For example, Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS) can only be used in a specific region.

Availability zone-specific services: These services can only be used in a specific Availability Zone within a region. For example, Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3) buckets can be created in a specific Availability Zone.

Here is a list of some AWS services that are region specific and Availability zone specific:

Region-specific services:

Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS)
Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2)
Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3)
Amazon Elastic Block Store (EBS)
Amazon Virtual Private Cloud (VPC)
Amazon Route 53
Amazon CloudFront
Amazon Simple Notification Service (SNS)
Amazon Simple Queue Service (SQS)


Availability zone-specific services:

Amazon Elastic Load Balancing (ELB)
Amazon Redshift
Amazon DynamoDB
Amazon ElastiCache
Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS) Multi-AZ deployments
It is important to note that not all AWS services are region specific or Availability zone specific. Some services, such as Amazon CloudWatch, can be used in any region or Availability Zone.


