A company needs to simultaneously process hundreds of requests from different users.
Which combination of AWS services should the company use to build an operationally efficient solution?

Here is the explanation:

Amazon SQS: Amazon SQS is a fully managed message queue service that can store and transmit messages between different system components. It is designed to handle high scalability and allows multiple requests to be queued and processed asynchronously, which is useful when there are a large amount of requests to be processed.

AWS Lambda: AWS Lambda is a serverless compute service that lets you run code in response to events. Can be triggered automatically by Amazon SQS when new messages arrive in the queue. Each request can be processed individually as a separate Lambda function, which allows for concurrent processing and on-demand scaling.

The most suitable combination of AWS services to handle the simultaneous processing of hundreds of requests from different users in an operationally efficient manner would be option A, which involves the use of Amazon Simple Queue Service (Amazon SQS) and AWS Lambda.
