The answer is B. Cost Explorer.

Cost Explorer is a tool in the AWS Billing and Cost Management console that allows you to visualize your AWS billing and usage data in a graphical format. You can use Cost Explorer to track your costs over time, identify trends, and find areas where you can save money.


for knowledge:
Cost Explorer also provides information about your AWS monthly costs. You can use this information to budget for your AWS spending and to track your actual spending against your budget.

AWS Bills and AWS Cost and Usage Report are both text-based reports that provide detailed information about your AWS billing and usage data. They are not as easy to use for visualizing your data as Cost Explorer.

AWS Budgets is a tool that allows you to set budgets for your AWS spending. It can help you to track your spending against your budget, but it does not provide any graphical visualization of your data.
