A company recently deployed an Amazon RDS instance in its VPC. The company needs to implement a stateful firewall to limit traffic to the private corporate network.
Which AWS service or feature should the company use to limit network traffic directly to its RDS instance?

Ans:Security groups
Security groups are used to control inbound and outbound traffic to and from an Amazon RDS instance. They are stateful, which means that they remember the state of connections and allow traffic to flow in both directions.

knowledge:
Network ACLs are used to control inbound and outbound traffic to and from a VPC. They are stateless, which means that they do not remember the state of connections and only allow traffic to flow in one direction.

AWS WAF is a web application firewall that is used to protect web applications from common web exploits. It is not used to control network traffic to and from Amazon RDS instances.

Amazon GuardDuty is a threat detection service that is used to identify and investigate potential threats to your AWS resources. It is not used to control network traffic to and from Amazon RDS instances.
==================
Which AWS service uses machine learning to help discover, monitor, and protect sensitive data that is stored in Amazon S3 buckets?
Amazon Macie

The AWS service that uses machine learning to help discover, monitor, and protect sensitive data that is stored in Amazon S3 buckets is Amazon Macie.

Amazon Macie is a fully managed data security service that uses machine learning to discover, classify, and protect sensitive data in AWS. It can automatically discover sensitive data in your Amazon S3 buckets, such as personally identifiable information (PII) and intellectual property (IP). Macie can also monitor your buckets for changes to sensitive data and generate alerts if it detects any suspicious activity.
==================
A company wants to improve the overall availability and performance of its applications that are hosted on AWS.
Which AWS service should the company use?
AWS Global Accelerator

AWS Global Accelerator is a networking service that helps improve the availability and performance of applications with a global user base. It provides static IP addresses that act as entry points to your application, routing user traffic to the nearest AWS edge location for low-latency and high-performance delivery.

By using AWS Global Accelerator, the company can benefit from improved availability and performance by leveraging the global AWS infrastructure. It intelligently routes traffic across multiple regions and edge locations, allowing users to access applications with reduced latency and improved response times.

knowledge
Amazon Connect: Amazon Connect is a cloud-based contact center platform that helps you to build and manage a contact center without the need for on-premises hardware or software. It offers a variety of features, such as call routing, voice recording, and chat, that can help you to improve the customer experience.
Amazon Lightsail: Amazon Lightsail is a fully managed compute platform that offers virtual machines, storage, and networking. It is a good choice for businesses that are looking for a simple and cost-effective way to host their applications.
