Which AWS service or feature identifies whether an Amazon S3 bucket or an IAM role has been shared with an external entity?
AWS IAM Access Analyzer.

AWS IAM Access Analyzer is a service that helps you to identify and remediate IAM policy issues, such as permissions that have been granted to external entities. It can identify whether an Amazon S3 bucket or an IAM role has been shared with an external entity by analyzing your IAM policies.
