A user wants to deploy a service to the AWS Cloud by using infrastructure-as-code (IaC) principles.
Which AWS service can be used to meet this requirement?
AWS CloudFormation

AWS CloudFormation is an infrastructure as code (IaC) service that allows you to create and manage AWS resources by using templates. A template is a text file that describes the resources that you want to create. You can use CloudFormation to deploy a service to the AWS Cloud by creating a template that specifies the AWS resources that you need, such as Amazon EC2 instances, Amazon S3 buckets, and Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS) databases.

AWS Systems Manager, AWS CodeCommit, and AWS Config are not IaC services. AWS Systems Manager is a service that helps you to automate tasks and manage your AWS resources. AWS CodeCommit is a service that provides a secure and highly scalable repository for storing code. AWS Config is a service that helps you to track and manage the configuration of your AWS resources.
