Use network ACLs

To restrict access to objects in Amazon S3, you can use bucket policies or access control lists (ACLs)12. Bucket policies define access to specific buckets and objects, while ACLs control access to individual objects in a bucket3. You can also use Amazon S3 Block Public Access as a centralized way to limit public access1.
