A company is designing its AWS workloads so that components can be updated regularly and so that changes can be made in small, reversible increments.
Which pillar of the AWS Well-Architected Framework does this design support?

The design of the company's AWS workloads supports the Operational Excellence pillar of the AWS Well-Architected Framework.

The Operational Excellence pillar focuses on designing and operating systems that are reliable, scalable, and secure. It includes practices such as:

Automating operations: Automating operations can help to reduce errors and improve efficiency.
Monitoring systems: Monitoring systems can help to identify and troubleshoot problems before they impact users.
Testing changes: Testing changes before they are deployed can help to reduce the risk of introducing errors.
Making frequent, small changes: Making frequent, small changes can help to reduce the risk of introducing major problems.
