==================
Which AWS tool or feature acts as a VPC firewall at the subnet level?
Network ACLs

A network access control list (ACL) is an optional layer of security for your VPC that acts as a firewall for controlling traffic in and out of one or more subnets1. You can associate a network ACL with multiple subnets; however, a subnet can be associated with only one network ACL at a time1.

Traffic Mirroring is a feature that allows you to copy traffic from one network interface to another. This can be used for troubleshooting or monitoring purposes.

An internet gateway is a network interface that allows your VPC to communicate with the internet. It is not a firewall and does not control the traffic that is allowed to flow in and out of your VPC.
==================
Which AWS service can be used to decouple applications?

Amazon SQS is a fully managed message queuing service that makes it easy to decouple and scale microservices, distributed systems, and serverless applications.

Amazon SQS provides a secure, reliable, and scalable way to decouple components of an application. Messages are stored in a queue until they are processed by the appropriate component. This allows the components to be scaled independently and to fail independently.

Knowledge:
AWS Config is a service that helps you to monitor and manage your AWS resources. It does not provide any functionality for decoupling applications.
AWS Batch is a service that helps you to run batch jobs on AWS. It does not provide any functionality for decoupling applications.
Amazon SES is a service that helps you to send email. It does not provide any functionality for decoupling applications.
==================
Which disaster recovery option is the LEAST expensive?

Backup and restore is the least expensive disaster recovery option because it does not require any additional hardware or software. It simply involves backing up your data and applications to a remote location and restoring them if your primary systems fail.

knowledge:
Warm standby is a more expensive option because it requires you to keep your secondary systems running, but not fully loaded. This means that you will need to pay for the hardware and software for your secondary systems, as well as the power and cooling costs.

Multisite is the most expensive option because it requires you to have your systems located in multiple geographical locations. This is necessary to protect your data and applications from disasters that can affect a single location.

Pilot light is a variation of warm standby where you only keep the bare minimum of infrastructure in your secondary location. This can be an even more cost-effective option than warm standby, but it may not be suitable for all businesses.
==================
Which type of AWS storage is ephemeral and is deleted when an Amazon EC2 instance is stopped or terminated?

Amazon EC2 instance store is a type of ephemeral storage that is attached to your instance when it is launched. The data on the instance store is deleted when your instance is stopped or terminated.

Knowledge:
Amazon EBS and Amazon S3 are persistent storage options, which means that your data is not deleted when your instance is stopped or terminated. Amazon EFS is a shared file system that can be used to store data that is shared between multiple instances.
==================
Which of the following is a characteristic of the AWS account root user?
The root user is the first sign-in identity that is available when an AWS account is created.
==================
