A company launched an Amazon EC2 instance with the latest Amazon Linux 2 Amazon Machine Image (AMI).
Which actions can a system administrator take to connect to the EC2 instance? (Choose two.)

Amazon EC2 Instance Connect and AWS Systems Manager Session Manager.

Amazon EC2 Instance Connect is a web-based tool that allows you to connect to your EC2 instances using SSH. It is a secure and easy way to connect to your instances, even if you do not have a public IP address for your instance.

AWS Systems Manager Session Manager is a service that allows you to connect to your EC2 instances using a secure shell (SSH) session. It is a more secure way to connect to your instances than using RDP or a direct SSH connection.

knowledge:
RDP is a protocol that allows you to connect to a remote computer and control it as if you were sitting in front of it. It is not a secure way to connect to your EC2 instances, and it is not supported by the latest Amazon Linux 2 AMI.

AWS Batch is a service that allows you to run batch jobs on AWS. It is not a way to connect to your EC2 instances.

Amazon Connect is a service that allows you to create and manage contact centers. It is not a way to connect to your EC2 instances.
