Under the AWS shared responsibility model, which task is the customer's responsibility when managing AWS Lambda functions?

Creating versions of Lambda functions

AWS Lambda is a service that lets customers run code without provisioning or managing servers. AWS Lambda automatically scales the resources according to the demand and only charges for the compute time consumed. AWS also provides and manages the Lambda runtime environment, which includes the operating system and the language interpreter2.

Therefore, the customer is responsible for creating versions of Lambda functions, which allows them to publish one or more copies of their function code and configuration as a version. Versions are immutable and have a unique Amazon Resource Name (ARN). Customers can use versions to manage their code deployment and rollback2. The other tasks are AWSâ€™s responsibility under the shared responsibility model.
