==================
A company has a serverless application that includes an Amazon API Gateway API, an AWS Lambda function, and an Amazon DynamoDB database.
Which AWS service can the company use to trace user requests as they move through the application's components?

AWS X-Ray

AWS X-Ray is a service that helps developers analyze and debug distributed applications. It provides a comprehensive view of how an application's components are performing, including the time it takes for each component to process a request.

AWS X-Ray can be used to trace user requests as they move through a serverless application. To do this, the developer needs to instrument the application's components with the AWS X-Ray SDK. When a user makes a request to the application, the AWS X-Ray SDK will generate a trace ID. This trace ID will be propagated through the application's components, and it will be used to correlate the performance of each component.

Once the request has been processed, the AWS X-Ray SDK will send the trace data to AWS X-Ray. AWS X-Ray will then store the trace data and make it available to the developer for analysis.

knowledge:
AWS CloudTrail is a service that logs all activity in your AWS account. It does not provide tracing capabilities.
Amazon CloudWatch is a monitoring and observability service. It can be used to collect and monitor metrics, logs, and events from your AWS resources. However, it does not provide tracing capabilities.
Amazon Inspector is a service that helps you identify and remediate security vulnerabilities in your AWS applications. It does not provide tracing capabilities.
