Which task does AWS perform automatically?
Encrypt data that is stored in Amazon DynamoDB

The correct answer is A. Encrypt data that is stored in Amazon DynamoDB. AWS automatically encrypts data at rest in Amazon DynamoDB using server-side encryption with AWS Key Management Service (AWS KMS) managed encryption keys1. This means that AWS handles the encryption and decryption of your data transparently, without requiring any changes to your application code.

knowledge:
AWS does not automatically patch Amazon EC2 instances, encrypt user network traffic, or create TLS certificates for usersâ€™ websites. These tasks are the responsibility of the user or can be done with the help of other AWS services. For example, you can use AWS Systems Manager Patch Manager to automate the process of patching your EC2 instances2. You can use AWS Certificate Manager to provision, manage, and deploy public and private SSL/TLS certificates for use with AWS services and your internal connected resources3. You can use AWS VPN or AWS Direct Connect to encrypt your network traffic between your on-premises network and AWS4.
