A. Resource controls
B. Cost allocation
C. Architecture optimization
D. Tagging enforcement

ANS:
Architecture optimization is the process of designing and managing your AWS infrastructure in a way that minimizes cost without sacrificing performance or reliability. This can involve a variety of strategies, such as choosing the right AWS services for your workloads, using Reserved Instances to save on long-term costs, and right-sizing your resources so that you are not overpaying for capacity that you do not need.
