What should you do in order to keep the data on EBS volumes safe

Use encryption: Encrypt your EBS volumes using EBS encryption or AWS Key Management Service (KMS) encryption. This will protect your data from unauthorized access even if the volume is compromised.
Use snapshots: Take regular snapshots of your EBS volumes. This will allow you to restore your data in the event of a failure or corruption.
Use lifecycle policies: Configure lifecycle policies to automatically delete old snapshots and volumes. This will help you to manage your storage costs and reduce the risk of data loss.
Monitor your EBS volumes: Use AWS CloudTrail to monitor all access to your EBS volumes. This will help you to identify any unauthorized activity and take corrective action.
Use security groups: Use security groups to restrict access to your EBS volumes. This will help to prevent unauthorized users from accessing your data.
==================
A company is deploying a new two-tier web application in AWS. Where should the most frequently accessed data be stored so that the applicationâ€™s response time is optimal?

The correct answer is D. Amazon ElastiCache.

Amazon ElastiCache is a managed in-memory data store that can be used to store frequently accessed data. This can significantly improve the performance of web applications by reducing the number of database queries that need to be made.

knowledge:
AWS OpsWorks: AWS OpsWorks is a managed application deployment platform. It is not designed for storing data.
AWS Storage Gateway: AWS Storage Gateway is a hybrid cloud storage service. It can be used to store data on-premises and in the cloud. However, it is not as well-suited for storing frequently accessed data as Amazon ElastiCache.
Amazon EBS volume: Amazon EBS volumes are block storage devices. They can be used to store any type of data, including frequently accessed data. However, they are not as fast as Amazon ElastiCache.
