A developer is planning to build a two-tier web application that has a MySQL database layer. Which of the following AWS database services would provide automated backups for the application?
Ans: Amazon Aurora.

Amazon Aurora is a MySQL-compatible relational database service that provides automated backups. Amazon Aurora automatically backs up your database every 5 minutes and stores the backups for up to 35 days. You can also restore your database to any point in time within the backup retention period.

Knowledge:
A MySQL database installed on an EC2 instance: You would need to "*manually create and manage backups of a MySQL database*" installed on an EC2 instance.
