What is trusted Advisor in AWS , what is the roles and responsiblity of that service

AWS Trusted Advisor is a service that provides recommendations for improving the security, performance, reliability, and cost-effectiveness of your AWS environment. Trusted Advisor uses a combination of AWS best practices and machine learning to identify areas where you can improve.

Trusted Advisor provides recommendations in four categories:

Security: Recommendations for improving the security of your AWS environment, such as implementing IAM best practices and using encryption.
Performance: Recommendations for improving the performance of your AWS environment, such as optimizing your EC2 instances and using caching.
Reliability: Recommendations for improving the reliability of your AWS environment, such as using Auto Scaling and CloudWatch alarms.
Cost: Recommendations for reducing the cost of your AWS environment, such as using reserved instances and spot instances.
Trusted Advisor is a free service that is available to all AWS customers. To use Trusted Advisor, you simply need to log in to the AWS Management Console and select Trusted Advisor from the menu.

The role and responsibility of Trusted Advisor is to help AWS customers improve their AWS environments. Trusted Advisor does this by providing recommendations for security, performance, reliability, and cost-effectiveness. Trusted Advisor's recommendations are based on AWS best practices and machine learning.

Here are some of the benefits of using AWS Trusted Advisor:

Improved security: Trusted Advisor can help you to identify and fix security vulnerabilities in your AWS environment.
Improved performance: Trusted Advisor can help you to optimize your AWS environment for performance.
Improved reliability: Trusted Advisor can help you to make your AWS environment more reliable.
Reduced costs: Trusted Advisor can help you to reduce the cost of your AWS environment.
==================
Which of the following is not a benefit of Amazon S3? (Choose TWO)

A. Amazon S3 provides unlimited storage for any type of data.
B. Amazon S3 can run any type of application or backend system.
C. Amazon S3 stores any number of objects, but with object size limits.
D. Amazon S3 can be scaled manually to store and retrieve any amount of data from anywhere.
E. Amazon S3 provides 99.999999999% (11 9â€™s) of data durability.
Answer
Correct answer: B, D
==================

What does AWS provide to deploy popular technologies such as IBM MQ on AWS with the least amount of effort and time?

AWS Quick Start reference deployments are pre-configured templates that you can use to deploy common AWS workloads. They are designed to be easy to use and deploy, and they can help you to get up and running with your AWS workload quickly and easily.

AWS Quick Start reference deployments are available for a variety of AWS workloads, including:

Web applications: AWS Quick Start reference deployments can be used to deploy web applications, such as WordPress, Drupal, and Joomla.
Databases: AWS Quick Start reference deployments can be used to deploy databases, such as MySQL, PostgreSQL, and Oracle.
Machine learning: AWS Quick Start reference deployments can be used to deploy machine learning workloads, such as Amazon SageMaker and Amazon Rekognition.
Networking: AWS Quick Start reference deployments can be used to deploy networking solutions, such as Amazon VPC and Amazon Route 53.
Storage: AWS Quick Start reference deployments can be used to deploy storage solutions, such as Amazon S3 and Amazon EBS.
