Under the Shared Responsibility Model, which of the following controls do customers fully inherit from AWS? (Choose TWO)

Ans:Patch management controls: Customers are responsible for patching the guest operating system (including updates and security patches) and other associated application software, while AWS is responsible for patching the underlying infrastructure that supports the AWS services 1.

Physical controls: AWS is responsible for the physical security of the facilities that run AWS Cloud services, while customers are responsible for the physical security of their own resources 1
