A developer needs to set up an SSL security certificate for a client's eCommerce website in order to use the HTTPS protocol. Which of the following AWS services can be used to deploy the required SSL server certificates? (Choose TWO)
Ans:
AWS ACM
AWS Identity & Access Management.

AWS ACM is a service that makes it easy to manage SSL/TLS certificates for your web applications and APIs. ACM can be used to provision, manage, and deploy certificates for your AWS resources, as well as for your on-premises resources.

AWS Identity & Access Management (IAM) is a service that provides secure access to AWS services and resources. IAM can be used to create and manage users, groups, and permissions for your AWS account.

To deploy an SSL server certificate using ACM and IAM, you would first need to create a certificate signing request (CSR) for your domain name. You can then use ACM to provision a certificate for your domain name. Once the certificate has been provisioned, you can use IAM to attach the certificate to your AWS resources.

Here are the steps involved in deploying an SSL server certificate using ACM and IAM:

Create a CSR for your domain name.
Provision a certificate for your domain name using ACM.
Attach the certificate to your AWS resources using IAM.
Once the certificate has been attached to your AWS resources, your eCommerce website will be using the HTTPS protocol.
