Which of the following approaches will help you eliminate human error and automate the process of creating and updating your AWS environment?
Ans:Use code to provision and operate your AWS infrastructure.
This can be done using a variety of tools and services, such as:

AWS CloudFormation: AWS CloudFormation is a service that helps you to automate the deployment and management of your AWS infrastructure using templates. CloudFormation templates can be used to create, update, and delete your infrastructure resources in a consistent and repeatable way.
AWS Terraform: AWS Terraform is an open-source infrastructure as code (IaC) tool that can be used to provision and manage your AWS infrastructure. Terraform templates can be used to create, update, and delete your infrastructure resources in a consistent and repeatable way.
AWS CodeDeploy: AWS CodeDeploy is a service that helps you to deploy, manage, and scale your applications. CodeDeploy can be used to deploy applications to a variety of AWS resources, such as EC2 instances, Lambda functions, and Elastic Beanstalk environments.
By using code to provision and operate your AWS infrastructure, you can eliminate human error and ensure that your infrastructure is always deployed and managed in a consistent and repeatable way.
