Which of the following is a type of MFA device that customers can use to protect their AWS resources?
U2F Security Key.
U2F security keys are physical devices that plug into a computer's USB port. When a user logs in to an AWS account, they are prompted to enter their username and password, and then to insert their U2F security key and press a button. This generates a one-time code that is used to authenticate the user.

U2F security keys are a very secure type of MFA device because they are difficult to counterfeit or steal. They are also easy to use and can be used with a variety of AWS services.
