Which of the below options is true of Amazon Cloud Directory?
Amazon Cloud Directory allows the organization of hierarchies of data across multiple dimensions.

AWS Directory Service is a set of services that help you to manage your directories in the AWS Cloud. Directory services provide a way to store and organize information about users, groups, and devices. This information can be used to control access to AWS resources and to manage your applications.

AWS Directory Service offers a variety of directory services, including:

AWS Directory Service for Microsoft Active Directory: This service allows you to run Microsoft Active Directory (AD) in the AWS Cloud. This can be useful if you want to migrate your existing AD environment to AWS or if you want to create a new AD environment in the AWS Cloud.
AWS Simple Active Directory: This service is a simplified version of AWS Directory Service for Microsoft Active Directory. It is a good choice for small businesses and organizations that are new to AWS.
AWS Managed Microsoft AD: This service is a fully managed version of AWS Directory Service for Microsoft Active Directory. It is a good choice for organizations that want to minimize the operational overhead of managing their own AD environment.
AWS Cloud Directory: This service is a cloud-native directory service that can be used to store and organize hierarchies of data. It is a good choice for applications that require a flexible directory structure.
