==================
Which of the following is a feature of Amazon RDS that performs automatic failover when the primary database fails to respond?

AWS RDS Multi AZ
RDS Multi-AZ is a deployment option that creates and maintains a primary database instance and at least one read replica instance in an Availability Zone (AZ). If the primary database instance fails, RDS Multi-AZ automatically fails over to one of the read replica instances.

knowledge:
RDS Single-AZ deploys a single database instance in a single AZ. If the database instance fails, the database is unavailable until the instance is restored.
RDS Write Replica creates a copy of a database instance that can be used to handle read traffic. Write replicas can be used to improve performance and scalability, but they do not perform automatic failover.
RDS Snapshots create a point-in-time copy of a database instance. Snapshots can be used to restore a database instance to a previous state, but they do not perform automatic failover.
