Which of the following has the greatest impact on cost? (Choose TWO)

ANS:A. Compute charges.
B. The number of services used.
C. Data Transfer In charges.
ANS:D. Data Transfer Out charges.
E. The number of IAM roles provisioned.


ANs:he two options that have the greatest impact on cost are:

Compute charges: Compute charges are the charges for using the CPU, memory, and storage resources of AWS services. Compute charges are typically the highest cost for AWS users.
Data Transfer Out charges: Data Transfer Out charges are the charges for transferring data from AWS to the internet. Data Transfer Out charges can be significant for applications that transfer a lot of data to users, such as streaming video applications and file-sharing applications.

knowledge:
The number of services used: The number of services that you use will have some impact on cost, but it is not typically the biggest cost factor.
Data Transfer In charges: Data Transfer In charges are the charges for transferring data from the internet to AWS. Data Transfer In charges are typically lower than Data Transfer Out charges.
