Which of the following is a managed AWS service that is used specifically for extract, transform, and load (ETL) data?

AWS Glue is a serverless data integration service that makes it easy to discover, prepare, move, and integrate data from multiple sources for analytics, machine learning (ML), and application development. AWS Glue provides a number of features that make it ideal for ETL workloads.

A visual development environment: AWS Glue Studio is a graphical user interface that makes it easy to create and run ETL pipelines.
A managed service: AWS Glue is a fully managed service, so you don't have to worry about managing or scaling the infrastructure required to run your ETL pipelines.
Support for a variety of data sources and destinations: AWS Glue supports a wide range of data sources and destinations, including relational databases, NoSQL databases, cloud storage, and on-premises systems.
A built-in library of ETL transformations: AWS Glue provides a built-in library of ETL transformations that you can use to cleanse, transform, and load your data.
