An ecommerce company has migrated its IT infrastructure from an on-premises data center to the AWS Cloud.
Which cost is the company's direct responsibility?
A. Cost of application software licenses
B. Cost of the hardware infrastructure on AWS
C. Cost of power for the AWS servers
D. Cost of physical security for the AWS data center

Ans:Cost of application software licenses

The cost that is the ecommerce company's direct responsibility is the cost of application software licenses.

The ecommerce company is responsible for the cost of all software licenses that it uses, regardless of whether the software is running on-premises or in the cloud. This includes the cost of licenses for operating systems, databases, and other applications.

The cost of the hardware infrastructure on AWS, the cost of power for the AWS servers, and the cost of physical security for the AWS data center are all borne by AWS.
