A company wants to set up an entire development and continuous delivery toolchain for coding, building, testing, and deploying code.
Which AWS service will meet these requirements?

AWS CodeStar is a cloud-based service that makes it easy for teams to develop, build, test, and deploy applications on AWS. CodeStar provides a unified user interface for managing all of the resources needed for a development and continuous delivery toolchain, including:

Source code management: CodeStar integrates with AWS CodeCommit, a fully managed Git-compatible service that hosts private repositories for source code and other assets.
Build: CodeStar integrates with AWS CodeBuild, a fully managed continuous build service that builds and tests source code.
Test: CodeStar integrates with AWS CodePipeline, a fully managed continuous delivery service that automates the release and deployment process.
Deploy: CodeStar integrates with AWS CodeDeploy, a fully managed deployment service

Knowledge:
Amazon CodeGuru: Amazon CodeGuru is a machine learning service that helps you improve the quality and security of your code. It is not a complete development and continuous delivery toolchain.
AWS CodeCommit: AWS CodeCommit is a fully managed Git-compatible service that hosts private repositories for source code and other assets. It is not a complete development and continuous delivery toolchain.
AWS CodeDeploy: AWS CodeDeploy is a fully managed deployment service that automates the deployment of applications to Amazon EC2 instances or Amazon Elastic Container Service (ECS) containers. It is not a complete development and continuous delivery toolchain.
