A retail company is building a new mobile app. The company is evaluating whether to build the app at an on-premises data center or in the AWS Cloud.
Which of the following are benefits of building this app in the AWS Cloud? (Choose two.)
Increased speed for trying out new projects
Flexibility to scale up in minutes as the application becomes popular
=================
What is an AWS Region?
 A physical location around the world where data centers are clustered
=================
Knowledge:
Edge locations

Edge locations are distributed around the world and are closer to end users than AWS Regions. This means that content and services delivered from edge locations can reach users faster with less latency. Edge locations are a good choice for applications that require low latency and high bandwidth, such as content delivery networks (CDNs), streaming video and gaming applications, real-time applications, and IoT applications.

Local zones

Local zones are a type of AWS infrastructure deployment that places compute, storage, database, and other select services closer to end users. Local zones deliver low latency and high bandwidth to applications that require local data processing, ultra-low latency access to AWS services, or local data storage. Local zones are a good choice for applications such as financial trading applications, healthcare applications, and media and entertainment applications.

Outposts

Outposts is a fully managed service that brings native AWS services, infrastructure, and operating models to virtually any data center, co-location space, or on-premises facility. Outposts makes it easy to extend AWS to on-premises environments. Outposts is a good choice for companies that need to run AWS services on-premises for reasons such as compliance, performance, or data residency requirements.

Conclusion

Edge locations, local zones, and outposts are all important parts of the AWS infrastructure. Edge locations help end users by delivering content and services with lower latency and higher bandwidth. Local zones and outposts help companies by providing them with the ability to run AWS services on-premises or in remote locations.
