A company wants to analyze streaming user data and respond to customer queries in real time.
Which AWS service can meet these requirements?
Amazon Kinesis Data Analytics
Amazon Kinesis Data Analytics is a fully managed service that makes it easy to process and analyze streaming data using SQL or Java (using Apache Flink). Kinesis Data Analytics can be used to build real-time data pipelines and applications, without having to learn new programming languages or processing frameworks.
=================
Which AWS service can help a company detect an outage of its website servers and redirect users to alternate servers?
AWS ROute 53
Amazon Route 53 is a highly available and scalable domain name system (DNS) web service. It can be used to detect an outage of website servers and redirect users to alternate servers or locations when the primary servers become unavailable. Route 53 offers a number of features that can help companies to improve the reliability and availability of their websites, including:

Health checks: Route 53 can be used to perform health checks on website servers to ensure that they are available and responding. If a server fails a health check, Route 53 can automatically route traffic to another server.
Failover routing: Route 53 can be used to implement failover routing, which automatically routes traffic to backup servers if the primary servers become unavailable.
Geolocation routing: Route 53 can be used to implement geolocation routing, which routes traffic to the servers that are closest to the user's location.
