A company that operates in the AWS Cloud wants to test workloads and team responses to simulated events. The company will conduct an exercise to identify potential issues that need to be addressed.

Which design principle of the AWS Well-Architected Framework does this exercise represent?
Anticipate failure

In the AWS Well-Architected Framework, the principle of "Anticipate failure" suggests that you should proactively simulate failures and test how your system responds to these failures. This includes conducting exercises and testing to identify potential issues and weaknesses in your architecture, application, and team's response to failures. The goal is to ensure that your system is resilient and can handle failures gracefully.
=================
Which AWS services provide high availability across multiple Availability Zones by default?
Amazon Elastic File System (Amazon EFS)
Amazon S3

Amazon EFS automatically stores data across multiple Availability Zones within a region to provide high availability and durability

S3 is region specific, but not availability zone specific. This means that when you create an S3 bucket, you must select a region for the bucket. However, S3 replicates your data across multiple availability zones within the region. This means that your data is always available, even if there is a problem with one availability zone.
